//IMG//

Which of the following changes should the tester apply to make the script work as intended?

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: B
this whole script is messed up, brackets are wrong etc. Even though perl is procedural, you can call a function before its declaration. Look at Finding Files script on this:
https://www.asc.ohio-state.edu/lewis.239/Class/Perl/perl.html
Example script:
#!/usr/bin/perl
$ip=$argv[1];
 attack($ip);
sub attack {
 print("x");
}

I will go with B

Selected Answer: A
#!/usr/bin/perl
$ip = "10.192.168.254";
if ($hostname eq "switchtest") {
 attack($ip);
}
else {
 exit 0;
}
